Northwest governors will, on Thursday in Kaduna, brainstorm on ways of improving agricultural practice for enhanced food security in Nigeria. A statement from the planning committee of the Arewa Research and Development Project said the governors would be part of a workshop for promoting collaboration on capacity development for agricultural research and development organized by the ARDP in collaboration with the Forum for Agricultural Research in Africa (FARA) and other agricultural finance/development/research bodies in Nigeria. The two-day workshop is expected to develop a matrix for partners, prioritize value chains, technologies and agribusiness pools for the activities of the regional bodies â€“FARA and South-South collaboration for capacity building and innovation work. It said the two-day workshop will galvanize different stakeholders for promoting collaboration to develop a matrix of partners, priority value chains technologies and agribusiness pools for different activities of the FARA led South-south collaboration for capacity building and innovation work.